# Commenting Standards

Key parts of the code must have comments explaining the "why" and "what".

## Guidelines

- **Classes and Functions**: Add a brief comment describing the purpose.
- **Complex Logic**: Explain complex algorithms or non-obvious logic.
- **Public Interfaces**: Document public methods and properties.
- **"Why" over "What"**: Focus on explaining *why* code is doing something, rather than just restating the code.

## Examples

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
const t = x * 0.15;

// ✅ GOOD
// Calculate tax based on the standard rate of 15%
const tax = income * 0.15;
```

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
function p(d) {
  // ...
}

// ✅ GOOD
/**
 * Processes the user data and updates the database.
 * @param data - The user input data
 */
function processUserData(data) {
  // ...
}
```
